The Blessed Lord said: He whose mind is fixed on My personal form, always engaged in worshiping Me with great and transcendental faith, is considered by Me to be most perfect.
PURPORTIn answer to Arjuna\xc3\x95s question, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa clearly says that he who concentrates upon His personal form and who worships Him with faith and devotion is to be considered most perfect in yoga. For one in such K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness there are no material activities because everything is done by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. A pure devotee is constantly engaged\xc3\x91sometimes he chants, sometimes he hears or reads books about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or sometimes he cooks pras\xe2\x88\x92dam or goes to the marketplace \nto purchase something for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or sometimes he washes the temple or the dishes\xc3\x91whatever he does, he does not let a single moment pass without devoting his activities to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa Such action is in full sam\xe2\x88\x92dhi.
